com.inqwell.any.channel

Class FIFO

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.inqwell.any.AbstractAny
      • com.inqwell.any.channel.AbstractChannelDriver
        • com.inqwell.any.channel.FIFO
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Any, ChannelDriver, Serializable

    public class FIFO
extends AbstractChannelDriver
implements ChannelDriver
    A channel driver that uses a com.inqwell.any.Queue to act as a buffer for communication. By default, items sent through the channel are deep-copied when the write() operation is called. This behaviour can be altered for those rare occasions where this is not necessary (for example when passing on an item de-serialized from a stream) by constructing the driver appropriately.

    Once the write() method completes, regardless of the buffer's copy mode, the buffer assumes exclusive ownership of the sent item. As such, when read() deals with a composite, only a shallow copy is performed.

    The maximum size of the buffer may be set according to specific requirements.

  • A size of zero (default) indicates that there is no maximum size. The queue can grow to an indefinite size.
  • A size of one will cause the participating threads to rendevous at the channel.
